      passage: `Students compared wild-type mice and knockout mice (with specific genes deactivated). Finding that knockout mice with the gene Asb5 deactivated tended to have lower blood sodium concentrations than wild-type mice, the students concluded that differences in circulating sodium level among house mice in nature are <u>solely</u> attributable to variations in the level of expression of Asb5.`,
